HEADWORD: Nassa
<hw>Nas"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Nassas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Nassae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[From L. <ets>nassa</ets> a kind of basket, in allusion to the
reticulation of some species.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species
of marine gastropods, of the genera <gen>Nassa</gen>, <gen>Tritia</gen>,
and other allied genera of the family <fam>Nassidae</fam>; a dog whelk.
See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Gastropoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>nas"soid</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
